comment._content: Is this a "duplicate" of this? "Ships of the Belcher expedition at anchor in Greenland, probably Disko Bay" by national maritime museum

comment.author: 11334970@N05
comment._content: Hi Pixel Wrangler, Although the images are very similar, they aren't duplicates. They're digital positive images of two separate calotype negatives. The brush strokes that you can see on the F6907-002 were made when sensitising the paper for the image to be taken. Also the camera has been moved very slightly and the icebergs are in slightly different positions.
